text: I'm usually a big fan of new romantic comedy movies so I expected Home Again to amuse me. Actually it didn't and my expectation turned out to be false.   The plot isn't complicated at all. It tells a story about a conscientious single mom Alice (Reese Witherspoon) who allowed three ambitious young men Harry (Pico Alexander), George (Jon Rudnitsky) and Teddy (Nat Wolff) to move in with her. After that everything in her life changed.  The acting is second-rate, except the child actors, they are great. The movie is also a bit unreal and not gripping at all. For example, Alice is able to put three strangers in her house, and at the same time be unemployed and raise two kids. Home Again isn't spectacular because it doesn't have any special effects. Although I genuienly didn't like the movie, it also has some good things. It's light-hearted and the ending is moving. Also, as I mentioned earlier, the child actors are great.  In conclusion, I don't think Home Again is worth seeing. I have seen a lot of rom-com movies, but it isn't something that stands out from the rest.
